# hiera-gc-autofix environments
#
# One environment per line. Blank lines and text after '#' are ignored.
# Fields are whitespace-separated:
#
#   repo_dir   [env]   [code_dir]
#
#   repo_dir   The git work tree the script fetches, resets, commits and
#              pushes from. It must contain a .gitreview file.
#   env        Optional. The environment name passed to hiera-gc --env.
#   code_dir   Optional. Passed to hiera-gc --code-dir.
#
# The script auto-detects the layout of each checkout:
#
#   * Self-environment checkout: repo_dir is itself an environment (it has a
#     hiera.yaml at its root, alongside data/, manifests/, modules/). This is
#     the common r10k dev-environment case. The environment name is the
#     directory name, the parent directory is used as the environments root
#     (hiera-gc --env-dir), and code_dir defaults to /etc/puppetlabs/code so
#     global modules and shared hieradata are visible. For these, repo_dir
#     alone is enough; env is taken from the directory name.
#
#   * Full code tree: repo_dir contains environments/<env>. Give the env name;
#     code_dir defaults to repo_dir.
#
# These should be deployed automation clones (modules resolved into modules/,
# or available in the global modules dir), since each run hard-resets the
# checkout to the Gerrit branch tip.

# Self-environment r10k dev-environment checkouts (env = directory name):
/etc/puppetlabs/code/dev_environments/sam_ardctest_default
/etc/puppetlabs/code/dev_environments/sam_rctest_default

# A full code tree where the env lives at environments/production:
# /srv/puppet-autofix/control-repo   production
